parameters: \n<Soldier's voice>"Don't falter! Push them back! Push them baaack!"
\n<Soldier a>"Damn it! How many of them are there?!"
\n<Soldier b>"This isn't something we can overcome with just spirit...!"
\n<Soldier c>"--They're coming again! Everyone, brace yourselves--!!"
\n<Soldier a>"Whose magic was that just now?! Who did it?!"

\n<Lyric>"...Seriously, this is complicated. I'm technically a
monster too, you know."
\n<Soldier a>"Who is that woman... Did she cast that magic earlier?"
\n<Soldier b>"Be careful! She might be an enemy!"
\n<??>"--She is an ally. Everyone, lower your swords."

\n<Soldier a>"...An ally? You're not citizens of Annabern. Who exactly
are you?"

\n<Roselitte>"...I am Roselitte Schwarz of the Royal Guard's Twelve
Knights. Who is in command here?"

\n<Soldier a>"A member of the Royal Knights--Lady Roselitte?! Ah...!
Indeed, that is your appearance...!"
\n<Captain>"My apologies! I am in command of the troops here!"

\n<Captain>"Suddenly, a horde of monsters appeared from the east,
surrounding Annabern and launching a full-scale attack!
Currently, all stationed soldiers are defending the town!"

\n<Captain>"However, some monsters have managed to infiltrate the town,
and we are dispatching troops to sweep them out, but the
situation is still unclear!"
\n<Roselitte>"What about the evacuation of the residents?"

\n<Captain>"We... We didn't make it in time...! By the time we
realized, we were already surrounded by a significant number
of monsters, and securing evacuation routes was
impossible... I'm terribly sorry...!"
\n<Ameria>"That's terrible...! There are so many people in Annabern!"
\n<Roselitte>"Acting rashly now might only lead to more danger..."

\n<Roselitte>"--Lyric. Is there any way to stop the monster taming
magic?"

\n<Lyric>"Monster taming magic involves interfering with each monster
individually, manipulating their consciousness and
perception. It's one thing to handle a few, but to control
many requires being relatively close to manage."

\n<Lyric>"There's a practitioner of monster taming magic nearby... No
doubt about it. It's Deorc. If we defeat him, I think we can
stop the monsters."
\n<Roselitte>"Is that true? Do you know where Deorc is?"
\n<Lyric>"I have an idea. It's vague, but yeah."

\n<Roselitte>"Captain. Prepare some skilled soldiers and supplies like
medicine immediately. We're going to strike at the source
controlling the monsters."

\n<Roselitte>"--Valam soldiers! I will take on the task of subduing the
monsters. You prioritize protecting the residents and
rebuild a solid defensive line!"

\n<Roselitte>"Lyric, tell me where Deorc is. And make sure to take Ameria
to a safe place."
\n<Ameria>"Lady Roselitte! I want to go too! I want to come with you!"

\n<Roselitte>"...Your company ends here. From this point on, it's a
soldier's duty."

\n<Roselitte>"We have a responsibility to protect the civilians. Your
safety is our top priority, and taking you to a dangerous
place is out of the question."

\n<Roselitte>"All the more reason. The town will need your skills soon.
We cannot afford to expose you to danger."
\n<Roselitte>"The other soldiers would say the same. Now, do as I say."
\n<Roselitte>"I understand your desire to fight... but no more..."
\n<Roselitte>"Don't make me feel ashamed any further."
\n<Roselitte>"Lyric, take Ameria to a safe place."
\n<Lyric>"...Understood. But I'm coming with you. If you refuse--"

\n<Soldier>"We will accompany you on the mission! Please give us your
orders!"

\n<Soldier>"Sir... Due to a sudden monster attack, many soldiers and
civilians in town are injured. Moreover, the medical
supplies being transported were destroyed by the monsters,
and we're having trouble with resupplying."

\n<Soldier>"The supplies we've managed to prepare are only this much...
I apologize for speaking out of turn. Please be extra
cautious going forward."

\n<Ameria>"Excuse me! I can use healing magic! Leave the treatment to
me!"

\n<Soldiers>"Oh! Is that true, little one?","Can you fight? We have few
medics who can stand on the front lines. Come with
us!","This is great, we can fight properly now!"

\n<Lyric>"Ahahahaha... Ah-, yes yes. Ameria, right. Don't worry, I'll
keep an eye on her. Leave it to me."

\n<Roselitte>"...From here on out, it's your responsibility no matter
what happens. Understood?"
\n<Ameria>"...It's okay. But leave it to me."
